"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses library scikit-learn. The issue lies in the way the ColumnTransformer is used with the Pipeline. The OneHotEncoder in the ColumnTransformer will output a numpy array with more features than the original DataFrame (because it one-hot encodes categorical variables), but the GaussianNB algorithm does not know the new feature names. However, the main issue here is that the GaussianNB does not support categorical features. It is designed for continuous data and works best with it.\",\n  \"patch\": \"24,27c24,27\\n  pipeline = Pipeline([\\n    ('prep', preprocessor),\\n    ('algo', GaussianNB())\\n  ])\\n---\\n  from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\\n  pipeline = Pipeline([\\n    ('prep', preprocessor),\\n    ('algo', MultinomialNB())\\n  ])\"\n}"